The objective of this prototype test plan is to make sure we address the most critical components of our glue dispensing jig for novel polymer mircochannel heat exchangers. To do this, the top 5 at-risk components from our Design Failure Mode Analysis (DFMEA) have been selected for further analysis. The components in order of highest to lowest risk are as follows: the adhesives life cycle, the MPHX jig's linearity, issues with adhesive bonding the jigs together, the lamina ridges interfering with the jig stacking, and the feed bearings being misaligned. These components can be further reduced to 3 main tests, adhesive testing, jig (both lamina and MPHX) testing, and a complete run through of the roller system. The following test plan will cover how we plan on testing the highest failure modes to make sure the glue dispensing jig runs smoothly.

